Three Moldovan utilities have
invited bids for a water development project co-financed by the
European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, SeeNews cited
by bank as saying.  Funding for six towns in the water system modernization
program includes 10 million euros ($13.3 million) from the EBRD
and loans for the same amount each from the  European Investment
Bank  and the EUâ€™s Neighbourhood Investment Facility, the news
